Class GenericArrayListHashMap<Value,​Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>>

java.lang.Object
abstractDataTypesImplemented.GenericArrayListHashMap<Value,​Key>
Type Parameters:
Value - type elements.
Key - keys that are going to get hashed and then used as index.
All Implemented Interfaces:
HashMapADT<Value,​Key>, java.lang.Iterable<Value>
public class GenericArrayListHashMap<Value,​Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements HashMapADT<Value,​Key>
Implementation of HashMapADT made with ArrayList. This uses an ArrayList inside of the hash map to fix collisions. Experimental version.
Author:
Borja Moralejo Tobajas
